parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's gauges will turn off while driving
the speedometer
odometer
tachometer
and fuel gauge will all zero out
the headlights and interior lights will flicker or shut off
the vehicle will stall or shut off while driving
the check engine light will appear
and the vehicle may have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The key will not turn in the ignition
the vehicle will not start
the vehicle will stall or shut off while driving
the dashboard lights will flicker or shut off
and the vehicle may have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle will stall or shut off while driving
the fuel pump will not turn on
the starter will not engage
and the vehicle may have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuses and wiring can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuses will blow
the dashboard lights will flicker or shut off
the vehicle's electrical system will malfunction
and the vehicle may have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior door handles can cause passengers to become trapped in the vehicle, leading to serious injury or death in emergency situations.
symptoms: Broken or cracked door handles
doors becoming inoperable from the inside
difficulty or inability to exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden and unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates suddenly and powerfully
even when the brake pedal is applied.
